These benchmarks are used to compare several n-ary product implementation
against the binary product.

Follow these instructions to produce the benchmarks:

1) Install git and python3 if it not already done.

2) Compile Spot and install if it is not already done.

3) Run the benchmarks

   % ./run

   This will build a CSV file called "result" respecting the following format:
        "datetime,version,nb_automata,nb_states,nb_densities,nb_ap,time"

You can run the benchmarks using the following options

  % ./run [--binary|--no-binary] [--states Q] [--automata N] [--density D]
          [--ap A] [--iterations I]

--binary|--no-binary: Run or not the benchmarks for the binary product
--states Q: Set the maximum number Q of states for an automaton
--automata N: Set the maximum number N of automata in an n-ary product
--density D: Set the maximum number D of densities benchmarkes
--ap A: Set the maximum number N of atomic propositions in an automaton
--iterations I: Set the maximum I of iterations used by the Python module timeit
